diff:1620187096:1620187096:=1,40d0%0a%3c :Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a%3c :Expansion: Discrimination against Spanish speakers in public places%0a%3c :Author: rajeev_g%0a%3c :Original: [[Articles.DoNotSpeakChineseInUniversityLounges|DoNotSpeakChineseInUniversityLounges]] %0a%3c :OriginalAuthor: [[Profiles.xiranw|xiranw]]%0a%3c :Section: A%0a%3c :Completed: 04.05.2021 - 20:58%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeExpansion:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25red%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25red%25 '''Comments to student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c I was reminded of a similar incident that took place a couple years ago in New York City, where the language in question was Spanish. There was an American English-speaking white lawyer in line at a store who became very upset that the Spanish-speaking employees were speaking in Spanish to the Spanish-speaking customers. He proceeded to berate the manager for the conduct of his employees and threaten to call ICE on the employees. While it's problematic enough that he believed that speaking a language that both speakers agree to use is offensive to him somehow, the idea that all Spanish-speaking Americans are undocumented perpetrates linguistic stereotypes. In addition, the idea that one's cultural identity could be weaponized as a tool to challenge one's legal status is reflective of a system that sees diversity of language and culture not as a strength, but as something to be eliminated.%0a%3c %0a%3c Source: https://www.vox.com/identities/2018/5/16/17362712/white-man-lawyer-threatens-spanish-speaking-workers-new-york-aaron-schlossberg%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:Category:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
